==English==

===Etymology===
From [[w:Old English language|Old English]][[category:Old English derivations]] [[sesoun]], [[w:French language|French]][[category:French derivations]] [[saison]], (meaning properly, the sowing time), from [[w:Latin|Latin]][[Category:Latin derivations]] [[satio]] (meaning a sowing, a [[plant]]ing), from [[serere]], [[satum]], (to sow, plant); akin to English [[sow]], (meaning to scatter, as seed). 

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːzən|-iːzən]]

===Noun===
'''season''' (plural '''seasons''')

#<!--DefA-->Each of the four divisions of a [[year]]: [[spring]], [[summer]], [[autumn]] and [[winter]].
#<!--DefB-->A part of a year when something particular happens: ''[[mating]] season'', ''[[rainy]] season'', ''[[football]] season''.
#<!--DefC-->(Obsolete) that which gives [[relish]]
#:''You lack the season of all natures, sleep.'' [[w:Shakespeare|Shakespeare]][[Category:Shakespeare Quotes]]
#{{cricket}} the [[period]] over which a [[series]] of [[test match]]es are played

